Comment (src/views/admin/NotificationsView.vue:1335):
`loadHealth()` and `loadJobs()` are invoked on mount regardless of which tab the user views first. If the primary use case is managing configuration, this adds extra API calls and initial render work. Consider lazy-loading these datasets when their tabs are first activated (and/or only refreshing jobs when the Deliveries tab is active).
Implementation guidance: In src/views/admin/NotificationsView.vue, update the auto-refresh behavior so jobs refresh only while the Deliveries tab is active. Add a small helper such as stopAutoRefreshJobsTimer() to clear autoRefreshTimer, and update the watch(autoRefreshJobs, ...) callback to start the interval only when enabled and activeTab.value === 'deliveries'. Inside the interval callback, guard with if (activeTab.value !== 'deliveries') return; before calling loadJobs() so a stale interval cannot fetch after tab changes. Add or update a watch(activeTab, ...) so leaving Deliveries clears the interval, and returning to Deliveries restarts it only if autoRefreshJobs.value is still true. Keep onUnmounted clearing the timer. Do not uncheck autoRefreshJobs automatically unless the product wants the checkbox state reset; the important behavior is to pause network calls outside the Deliveries tab.
Implementation guidance: In src/views/admin/NotificationsView.vue, change the initial data-loading strategy so tab-specific datasets are lazy-loaded when their tabs are opened. Keep loadSlackDestinationStatus() in onMounted() for the default Configuration tab, but remove unconditional loadHealth() and loadJobs() from onMounted(). Add state flags such as hasLoadedHealth and hasLoadedJobs (or equivalent) that are set after the first successful or attempted load, then add a watch(activeTab, ...) that calls loadHealth() the first time activeTab becomes 'health' and loadJobs() the first time activeTab becomes 'deliveries'. When linkToDeliveries(filter) switches to Deliveries and sets jobIdOrCorrelationFilter, ensure loadJobs() runs for that filtered view even if jobs were not previously loaded; avoid calling loadJobs() before the filter ref has been updated. Preserve explicit refresh buttons and filter actions so they still call loadHealth()/loadJobs() on demand.
